{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Use British English|date=March 2017}} {{Other uses|Castle Street (disambiguation){{!}}Castle Street}}
[[File:Cambridge & County Folk Museum - geograph.org.uk - 631123.jpg|thumb|The [[Museum of Cambridge]], on the corner of Castle Street and [[Northampton Street, Cambridge|Northampton Street]].]]
'''Castle Street''' is a street in the north of central [[Cambridge]], England.<ref>[http://www.cambridgeonline.co.uk/streets/Castle_Street/ Castle Street], [http://www.cambridgeonline.co.uk/ Cambridge Online].</ref><ref name="openguides">[http://cambridge.openguides.org/wiki/?Locale_Castle_Street Locale Castle Street], [http://cambridge.openguides.org/ The Open Guide to Cambridge].</ref> To the southeast is a junction with [[Northampton Street, Cambridge|Northampton Street]], [[Magdalene Street]], and [[Chesterton Lane, Cambridge|Chesterton Lane]] (leading to [[Chesterton Road, Cambridge|Chesterton Road]]). To the northwest is a junction with [[Mount Pleasant, Cambridge|Mount Pleasant]], [[Huntingdon Road]] (leading northwest out of Cambridge), [[Histon Road]] (leading north out of Cambridge), and [[Victoria Road, Cambridge|Victoria Road]].<ref>[http://www.cambridge2000.com/cambridge1950/html/histon.html Cambridge 1950: Histon Road — Huntingdon Road — Victoria Road junction], [http://www.cambridge2000.com/cambridge1950/ Cambridge 1950].</ref>
To the northeast is [[St Giles' Church, Cambridge|St Giles' Church]], [[Castle Hill, Cambridge|Castle Hill]], the location of [[Cambridge Castle]], and the [[Cambridgeshire]] Shire Hall. To the southwest is [[St Peter's Church, Cambridge|St Peter's Church]] and Honey Hill. On the corner of Castle Street and Northampton Street is the [[Museum of Cambridge]], formerly the Cambridge & County Folk Museum.<ref>{{cite web|title=the folk museum is changing its name!|url=http://www.folkmuseum.org.uk/page.php?id=292|work=www.folkmuseum.org|accessdate=17 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130807165859/http://folkmuseum.org.uk/page.php?id=292#|archive-date=7 August 2013|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Also here is [[Kettle's Yard]], a former home and now a modern [[art gallery]] and place for reflection.<ref>[http://www.donowdo.com/Art-Craft-And-Sculpture-Galleries/Kettles-Yard-Cambridge-CB3-0AQ.htm Kettle's Yard, Castle Street, Cambridge] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20081024140817/http://www.donowdo.com/Art-Craft-And-Sculpture-Galleries/Kettles-Yard-Cambridge-CB3-0AQ.htm |date=24 October 2008 }}, [http://www.donowdo.com/ doNOWdo].</ref>
[[St Giles' Church, Cambridge|St Giles' Church]], [[St Peter's Church, Cambridge|St Peter's Church]] and [[Castle Street Methodist Church]] are beside the street.<ref>[http://www.castlestreet.org.uk/ Castle Street Methodist Church].</ref> The Castle Inn public house is also located here.<ref name="openguides" />
