=== Prix Versailles 2018 – World winners === The awards were conferred at [[UNESCO]] Headquarters on 15 May 2018. Twelve world winners were recognized in four categories, selected from amongst 70 continental winners from 32 countries.<ref>[https://www.archdaily.com/895401/world-winners-of-2018-prix-versailles-awards-announced World Winners of 2018 Prix Versailles Awards Announced]</ref><ref>[https://docs.wixstatic.com/ugd/840afa_510ada0ac66c49a3827aa59e915ccb70.pdf Press release from 18 May 2018] (accessed on 29 October 2018)</ref><ref>[[International Union of Architects]], [https://competition.uia-architectes.org//en/competitions/4eme-edition-du-prix-versailles.html Prix Versailles 2018] (accessed on 18 August 2018)</ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center; width: 100%;" ! width="10%" | Prix or special prize || width="10%" | Category || width="22%" | Project || width="16%" | Location || width="10%" | Country || width="22%" | Architect or designer || width="10%" | Country |- | Prix Versailles | Shops & Stores | ''[[Apple]] Orchard Road'' | [[Singapore]] | Singapore | ''[[Foster + Partners]]'' | United Kingdom |- | Special prize Interior | Shops & Stores | ''[[Dolce & Gabbana|Dolce Gabbana]]'s Venice Palazzo'' | [[Venice]] | Italy | ''Carbondale'' | France |- | Special prize Exterior | Shops & Stores | ''[[Porcelanosa]] Chile'' | [[Santiago]] | Chile | ''Gonzalo Mardones Arquitecto'' | Chile |- | Prix Versailles | Shopping Malls | ''Watermark [[Westquay]]'' | [[Southampton]] | United Kingdom | ''acme / [[Hammerson]]'' | United Kingdom |- | Special prize Interior | Shopping Malls | ''Lane 189'' | [[Shanghai]] | China | ''[[UNStudio]]'' | Netherlands |- | Special prize Exterior | Shopping Malls | ''[[McArthurGlen Group|McArthurGlen]] Provence'' | [[Miramas]] | France | ''Marseille Architecture Partenaires'' | France |- | Prix Versailles | Hotels | ''[[Aman Resorts|Aman]]yangyun'' | [[Shanghai]] | China | ''[[Kerry Hill]] Architects'' | Singapore |- | Specia